                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/20149</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-26T16:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 26, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reactionaries entered town of Soledad on the Mexican Railway about 27 miles from
                    Vera Cruz yesterday, defeated Carranza forces and took ammunition stored
                    there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
